*.swp
*.swo
*~
.env
.env.local
node_modules/
.state/

# In consumer repos, `/spade-onboard` injects committed copies of the
# framework's docs and examples under `.spade/docs/` and `.spade/examples/`.
# In THIS repo (the framework itself) the canonical copies under `docs/`
# and `examples/` are the source of truth, so we ignore any residual
# `.spade/docs/` or `.spade/examples/` that a local pre-guard onboarding
# run may have created. Bundle A's self-onboard guard prevents this
# going forward; this is belt-and-braces.
.spade/docs/
.spade/examples/

# Private learnings are captured by `/spade-learn` when the human
# classifies an entry as NOT public-safe. They stay on local disk for
# the team but must never be committed — they may reference internal
# systems, credentials paths, or security details that should not leak
# into public forks. See .claude/skills/spade-learn/SKILL.md.
.spade/learnings/private/
